      • getExtent

        public Extent getExtent()

        Gets the bounding box in world coordinates. If the layer has defined the BoundingBox tag, we will take this bounding box as entire extension of this layer, else we'll see if the tag WGS84BoundingBox is defined (it can be approximated). In this case we'll take WGS84BoundingBox as entire extension.


        Note:

        If the layer has grid subsets (TileMatrixLimits) then this will have a only extent but if the layer doesn't have grid subsets then this will have a different extent in each level resolution. In this case we need to know the extent for each level.

        Specified by:
        getExtent in interface RasterProvider
        Overrides:
        getExtent in class AbstractRasterProvider
        Returns:
        Extent

      • getFileLayer

        public File getFileLayer()
                  throws RasterDriverException
        When the remote layer has fixed size this method downloads the file and return its reference. File layer has in the long side FIXED_SIZE pixels and the bounding box is complete. This file could be useful to build an histogram or calculate statistics. This represents a sample of data.

      • readBlock

        public Object readBlock(int pos,
                        int blockHeight,
                        double scale)
                 throws InvalidSetViewException,
                        FileNotOpenException,
                        RasterDriverException,
                        ProcessInterruptedException
        Reads a complete block of data and returns an tridimensional array of the right type. This function is useful to read a file very fast without setting a view. In a WMTS service when the size is fixed then it will read the entire image but when the source hasn't pixel size it will read a sample of data. This set of data will have the size defined in FIXED_SIZE.
        Specified by:
        readBlock in interface RasterProvider
        Parameters:
        pos - Posición donde se empieza a leer
        blockHeight - Altura máxima del bloque leido
        Returns:
        Object que es un array tridimendional del tipo de datos del raster. (Bandas X Filas X Columnas)
        Throws:
        InvalidSetViewException
        FileNotOpenException
        RasterDriverException
        ProcessInterruptedException
